records.addlTxt:
Defendant in custody.   
State files an Amended Information amending Count 5 to 3rd degree sexual assault, contrary to Section 940.225(3) of the Wisconsin Statutes.   Motion granted.   
Count 3 - Contribute to delinquency of child - Guilty plea.   
Count 5 - 3rd degree sexual assault - Guilty plea.   
Count 10 - Felony bail jumping - Guilty plea.    Convicted.   Sentences are withheld.   On the felony Counts 5 and 10 - Sentences are withheld.   Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for four (4) years.    
On the misdemeanor count 3 - Sentence is withheld.   Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for one (1) year.    Conditions of probation are:
1) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process; 
2) Comply with sex offender treatment; 
3) No contact with the victims: AV (02-27-02); BD (04-11-2000); LMA (08-15-01);
4) Comply with any paternity testing and child support order regarding minor child of BD;
5) No contact with anyone under the age of 18 unless approved by the agent, with the exception of his minor child with BD and 3rd party contact with BD;
6) Maintain full-time employment, schooling or combination thereof;
7) Maintain absolute sobriety;
8) No use or possession of any internet enabled device without agent's approval;
9) No use or possession of smartphone;
10) No use of social media applications or websites;
11) Must register all current and past usernames, passwords and online accounts with agent;
12) On felony counts, spend six (6) months in jail, under the Huber Law, to commence today;
13) Submit DNA sample and pay surcharges;
14) Pay costs of action; 
15) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.  
Defendant is entitled to 57 days sentence credit if revoked.   
Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights. 
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief.  
Minutes.

Stipulation and Order Regarding HIV/STD Testing Pursuant to Sec. 968.38 Wis. Stats.
The Court hereby orders:
1) the defendant shall submit to an HIV test and to test or series of tests to detect the presence of any sexually transmitted disease;
2) the tests shall be performed by a health care professional;
3) the court shall require the health care professional who performs the test to disclose the results to the defendant, to refrain from making the test results part of the defendant's permanent medical record, and to disclose the results of the test to the alleged victim or her parent or guardian;
4) the defendant shall reimburse the Manitowoc County Jail for any expenses incurred for the testing.
Copy to jail.
